

1. Project Title

Sales Data Modeling using Power BI

2. Schema Type

Star Schema

3. Explanation

This project is based on designing an efficient data model using Power
BI. A Star Schema approach is used where a central fact table (Sales) is
connected to multiple dimension tables such as Date, Product, Customer,
and Region.

The Sales table contains transactional data including Sales Amount,
Cost, Quantity, and Dates. Dimension tables provide descriptive
information to support analysis.

Relationships are created as One-to-Many between dimension tables and
the fact table with single cross filter direction to ensure optimal
performance.

An inactive relationship is implemented using Return Date to analyze
returned transactions. This is activated using the USERELATIONSHIP
function in DAX.

Hierarchies are created for Date (Year → Quarter → Month → Day), Product
(Category → Subcategory → Product), and Region (Country → State → City)
to allow drill-down analysis.

Data cleaning is performed using Power Query by removing null values,
correcting data types, and eliminating duplicates.

Test visuals such as bar charts, line charts, and cards are created to
validate the model and ensure correct working of relationships and
measures.

Overall, this project demonstrates proper data modeling, DAX usage, and
report building in Power BI.
